listJob.description:
Are you passionate about ensuring the quality, reliability, and performance of cutting-edge systems? Do you thrive in environments driven by innovation in AI-driven software development? Join Renn Labs, where your enthusiasm meets high-energy, collaborative, and forward-thinking tech innovation. We're on the lookout for a skilled QA/QC Engineer to play a key role in enhancing the technological excellence of our innovative AI applications. This is more than a job ‚Äì it's a chance to be at the forefront of technological advancement with a team that values creativity and innovation.
 The QA/QC Engineer is a crucial role, responsible for working closely with product managers, designers, and engineers to establish, enforce and implement quality assurance standards and practices. This position is central to our software product development, ensuring innovation is matched with exceptional quality and reliability.
Ready to elevate your value to new heights and redefine the future? Uplift your Test Engineering journey with Renn Labs today.
 IN DETAIL, YOUR SUCCESS IN THIS JOB WILL BE
  Effectively developing and executing detailed test plans and test cases for both new features and regression testing, balancing manual and automated testing strategies to ensure comprehensive coverage;
Proactively working within the software engineers to identify potential issues / bugs early in the development cycle, aiming to prevent defects before deployment;
Efficiently implementing and maintaining automated tests within our CI/CD pipeline, contributing to streamlined and reliable testing processes.
Continuously engaging in learning to stay updated with the latest QA technologies and practices, applying this knowledge to systematically improve our testing framework;
Diligently supporting the development of testing standards and procedures to ensure continuous improvement in quality and efficiency across projects;
Thoroughly assisting in troubleshooting and resolving defects, providing detailed documentation and feedback to the development team to ensure timely resolutions;
Actively participating in agile development processes, including inceptions, planning, daily check-ins, reviews and retros, contributing a quality perspective to each phase with constructive insights;
Promptly comprehend the business flow and logic for each product to seamlessly transition across diverse projects while maintaining constant work effectiveness. This entails quickly understanding the unique requirements and challenges of each project to ensure quality assurance practices are effectively adapted and applied;
Timely and efficiently  troubleshooting and resolving any obstacles relating to the job.

listJob.jobExperience:
WHAT YOU‚ÄôLL NEED FOR SUCCESS IN THIS JOB
  Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent experience;
4+ years of experience in software quality assurance, demonstrating a strong foundation in both manual and automated testing; The designated title will be assigned per your strength and experience;
Knowledgeable in API testing tools (e.g., Postman) for validating backend services and ensuring integration points meet functional, performance, and security standards;
Familiarity with automated testing tools and frameworks (e.g., Selenium) and understanding of their integration into CI/CD pipelines;
Capability to write custom test scripts and automate routine tasks, thereby enhancing testing efficiency and coverage, or willingness to learn these skills along the way;
Deep knowledge of software development processes and a strong desire to learn and adapt to new technologies and methodologies;
Experience with database systems (SQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB) for testing data integrity and data-driven testing scenarios;
Effective communication skills, capable of working collaboratively within a cross-functional team and articulate technical issues and solutions clearly;
Proven problem-solving abilities, with a detail-oriented approach to testing and quality assurance;
Eagerness to take on new challenges and contribute to a team environment, with a commitment to continuous improvement and learning;
Experience with performance and security testing tools to assess and improve the scalability and security posture of applications will make an ideal candidate;
Demonstrated ability in taking part in multiple projects simultaneously will set your application apart and give you a distinct advantage;
Last but not least, an eagerness to learn and a startup spirit at heart. This role provides extensive exposure to AI-driven product development, offering a pathway to advance in the future of technology.

*** General requirements:
‚Ä¢ Bachelor degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Telecommunication Engineering, Mathematics, Mechanics and Informatics or equivalent.
‚Ä¢ Strong motivation to develop career in automotive software field.
‚Ä¢ Software development experience in C++ programming;
‚Ä¢ Having good knowledge with OOP, OOAD (Object-Oriented Analysis and Design);
‚Ä¢ Having hands-on experience to use JIRA, GIT and Gerrit;
‚Ä¢ Having hands-on experiences in developing large software systems;

* Highly talented & experienced candidates will be considered for Senior/Leader positions.
  *** These skills would be considered as an advantage but not the must:
‚Ä¢ Experiences related to multi-thread, multi-process programming;
‚Ä¢ Having hands-on experiences to use and implement design patterns (MVC, Singleton, Observers);
‚Ä¢ Experiences related to develop application using Qt/QML;
‚Ä¢ Experiences related to design and develop GUI frameworks, front-end applications;
‚Ä¢ Ability to effectively present information to top management, public groups, and/or board of directors.

